Populate the Dimension Tables 17

The data flow tasks are as follows


The data flow tasks in each of the dimension tables look like this:

OLE DB Source->Lookup Transformation(this is where the primary key in the ODS Layer is able to be uniquely identified so that we can bring along the appropriate information to store as a DimensionKey in the respective dimension table.)->Derived Column->OLE DB Destination. 


 The Detailed Breakdown is as follows:


We do the same steps we did for the ODS Layer of the data but before that lets get a couple easy ones out of the way.

Use the Stored Procedure to Generate the DimCalendarDay Data and the script included to populate the DimGeography Table. See below for guidance:

First Create the stored procedure using the code provided.



Then select and execute the highlighted portion below: 



Next just run the Geography Script and the table will be populated:


Now onto the next part.


Create an Execute SQL Task to truncate the data before loading.

Create a Data Flow Task next.



The Data Flow Task will look like this.



The steps are as follows:

Create an OLE DB Source. This will hold the Census Table we created in the ODS Layer.


We use the lookup transformation again and are bringing over key data to populate the Dimension Table for the appropriate subject.


Use the Derived Column Transformation and then we go to the final step.

Create an OLE DB Destination and this will be where we populate the Dimension table.

Be sure map everything correctly and choose the correct connection manager.


Run the package and you will have your first Dimension table populated. Do this for all remaining Dimension Tables. The steps will remain the same.
